# Final previous-button code

Use this as the final replacement:

```xhtml
<h:panelGroup id="previousNavigationPanel">

    <h:commandButton
        id="prvImg"
        styleClass="secondary"

        disabled="#{independentContactHistoryController
                    .viewEditFollowUpListBean.diablePrev}"

        action="#{independentContactHistoryController
                  .navigatePreviousContactHistory}"

        image="#{independentContactHistoryController
                 .viewEditFollowUpListBean.diablePrev
                 ? resource['images:common/button-previous-disabled.png']
                 : resource['images:common/button-previous.png']}"

        alt="Previous contact history"
        title="Previous contact history">

        <p:ajax
            process="@form"

            update=":viewEditContactHistoryForm:editFollowupNoteMainID
                    :viewEditContactHistoryForm:contactViewEditSaveCloseButtonsPanelID
                    :viewEditContactHistoryForm:previousNavigationPanel
                    :editCloseFollowUpConfirmDialog"

            oncomplete="handlePreviousNavigationComplete(args)"/>

    </h:commandButton>

</h:panelGroup>
```

# Why this is now the better approach

```text
Old RichFaces
<a:commandButton image="...">
          ↓
Generated input type="image"

Jakarta Faces 4
<h:commandButton image="...">
          ↓
Generated input type="image"
```

This preserves:

* The existing image files.
* The existing `.secondary` CSS.
* The existing page positioning.
* The enabled/disabled button behavior.
* The existing Java action logic.
* PrimeFaces Ajax processing and updates.

Your current invisible-arrow problem should be solved first by testing this single static component:

```xhtml
<h:commandButton
    image="#{resource['images:common/button-previous.png']}"
    type="button"/>
```

